content.thinking:
The `.default({})` approach doesn't work because Zod sees required fields. Correct Zod pattern: mark sub-schema fields as `optional()` on the parent level. Actually, the right pattern is to use `.catchall(z.any())` or... no ŌĆö the real pattern is:

```ts
export const V1Schema = z.object({
  tts: TTSSchema.optional().default({}),
  ...
});
```

Each sub-schema field on the parent needs `.optional().default({})` so that `parse({})` works ŌĆö `{}` ŌåÆ `{}` for tts field ŌåÆ each field gets its default.

